 practices, Everyday Cosmopolitanisms brings the study of medieval Eurasia into relation with contemporary investigations of cosmopolitanism and globalization, challenging persistent divisions between modern and medieval, global and "idian.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aTrade routeszCaucasusxHistory. 7aHISTORY / World.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073915240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520380936zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520380936zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520380936/original  a978-3-11-073915-2 University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA